# One pkgsrc package origin (category/name) per line. These are packages the
# other Cross-Platform Action ports get from the official pkgsrc binary
# mirrors but that have no prebuilt vax builds.
#
# They are cross-compiled on a NetBSD/amd64 host (USE_CROSS_COMPILE=yes). The
# whole build-tool closure (perl, texinfo, bison) builds NATIVELY as
# tool-dependencies; only the target's own code is cross-compiled.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
shells/bash
net/rsync

# sudo's configure runs a second compiler probe (AX_PROG_CC_FOR_BUILD) for a
# native BUILD compiler. Without help it falls back to the pkgsrc wrapper `gcc`
# (which points at the vax cross-compiler) and fails ("cannot run C compiled
# programs"). cross-build.sh feeds it pkgsrc's ${NATIVE_CC} (/usr/bin/cc -B
# /usr/libexec -B /usr/bin) via CONFIGURE_ENV -- the -B flags force the native
# as/ld.
security/sudo

# curl links the base OpenSSL + zlib already in the vax sysroot (from build.sh
# distribution), so no target openssl/zlib build is needed. Its other vax
# runtime deps (libidn2, libunistring, libxml2, nghttp2, xmlcatmgr) cross-build
# on the same machinery.
www/curl
